de.digitalcollections.blueprints.crud.backend.impl.jpa.entity

Class SequenceConstants

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.digitalcollections.blueprints.crud.backend.impl.jpa.entity.SequenceConstants

  • public class SequenceConstants
extends Object
    Using a sequence-table (instead of hibernate_sequence) to prevent id conflicts when inserting rows without hibernate technology (we use Flyway on server start, where we use SQL-files or Spring-JDBC to insert data, before hibernate is started). When hibernate starts, it looks up new starting id before allocating IDs (based on allocation_size). Example with Strings instead constants: TableGenerator(name="TABLE_GEN", table="SEQUENCE_TABLE", pkColumnName="SEQ_NAME", valueColumnName="SEQ_COUNT", pkColumnValue="USER_SEQ")
